<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1279087 size-full" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Kidnapped.jpg?resize=640%2C377&#038;ssl=1" alt="Catholic, Enugu" width="640" height="377" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Kidnapped.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Kidnapped.jpg?resize=300%2C177&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Kidnapped.jpg?resize=768%2C452&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Kidnapped.jpg?resize=58%2C34&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Kidnapped.jpg?resize=260%2C153&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Kidnapped.jpg?resize=200%2C118&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Kidnapped.jpg?resize=560%2C330&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> In a renewed attack on priests in Enugu State, another Catholic Priest, Rev Fr Arinze Madu, of the Queen of Apostles Seminary, Imezi-Owa, Ezeagu local government area of Enugu has been abducted by gunmen. Enugu Catholic Diocese which confirmed the story said it it has been devastated since the abduction on Monday. Director of the Diocese communication, Rev Fr Been Achi told Vanguard that “It’s heart-rendering, brings sadness and disappointment. It makes one sad the moment you think one is secured, almost to tell you that you’re not as secure. “The priest was just coming out of his house and he was accosted and abducted.” According to the state police command, the police is already in the trail to safely secure release of the clergy. Enugu police spokesman, Ebere Amaraizu, the command has intensified manhunt on the abductors
with a view to liberating victim unhurt and arresting suspects. It was gathered that the priest was abducted on Monday Evening at about 5.50 pm near the gate of the seminary located at Imezi Owa as he was driving out of the seminary premises after suspected hoodlums fired sporadically. Reacting to the development, the Enugu State Government expressed deep concern about the unfortunate incident and charged the Nigeria Police Force and other security agencies to ensure that the priest was rescued unhurt. The state government added that it “will leave no stone unturned to make sure that he regains his freedom.” The government reassured the people of its “commitment to continue to make the state safe and to sustain the enviable status of Enugu as one of the safest and most peaceful states in Nigeria.” Vanguard By Dennis Agbo Two days after the Catholic Priest of Queen of Apostles Seminary, Imezi Owa in Ezeagu Local Government Area, Enugu State, Rev Fr Arinze Madu was kidnapped, he has regained freedom. It was not clear at press time if any ransom was paid before he was released. ALSO… October 30, 2019 In "News" The Police Command in Enugu State says abducted Catholic Priest, Rev. Fr. Malachy Asadu, serving under Catholic Diocese of Nsukka, has been released. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) recalls that Asadu was abducted on Monday by unknown persons in Nsukka town. The Command’s Public Relations Officer, SP Ebere Amaraizu, who… November 27, 2019 In "Metro" The Enugu Police Command said Saturday in Enugu that it has commenced a massive manhunt of abductors of a Catholic Priest, Rev.-Fr. Theophilus Ndulue. November 16, 2019 In "News"